18 October 2012The annual meeting between Cabinet and the South African National Editors Forum (SANEF) is scheduled to take place this coming weekend. These meetings provide a strategic platform for government and the media to strengthen working relations as well as discuss issues of mutual interest aimed at reinforcing our democracy. Deputy President Kgalema Motlanthe will lead a Government delegation comprising of Ministers and Deputy Ministers, while the SANEF Chairperson Mr Mondli Makhanya will lead a group of senior editors from around the country. The meeting will take place at Mount Grace Country House and Spa on Friday 19th October and Saturday 20th October 2012 Members of the media are invited to the Friday 19th October 2012 session as follows: The opening session including remarks by Deputy President and Sanef Chairman A photo opportunity of the delegates. Media wishing to attend should kindly RSVP by sending details, i.e. name, contact details, I.D. or passport number to Pheliswa@gcis.gov.za or bongiwe@gcis.gov.za by 14h00 on 19 Friday October. All media must arrive at the venue by 17h00. Enquiries: Phumla Williams 083 501 0139 Issued by: Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) 